radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 1.0 cm, with adjacent inflammation and contains several tiny appendicoliths. The liver demonstrates diffusely low homogeneous attenuation throughout with no focal lesions. The gallbladder contains gallstones without wall thickening or surrounding inflammation. All other abdominal organs are unremarkable, and there is no evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation.
